CELESTINE OKAFOR ABUJA – Muhammed Adamu, the Inspector General of Police (IGP), has ordered a manhunt for the killers of Rev. Father Paul Offu, a Catholic Priest in charge of St. James the Greater Parish Catholic Church, Ugbawka, in Enugu State. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Mr Frank Mba, Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP), the Police Force Public Relations Officer (PFPRO), disclosed this through a statement on Saturday. He said crack detectives from the IGP-Intelligence Response Unit (IRT), the Forensic and Homicide sections of the Force Criminal Investigation Department (FCID) had been deployed to Enugu State to complement the command in their investigations into the unfortunate incident. Mba added that, the AIG in charge of Zone 9 Headquarters had been directed to mobilise more units of Police Mobile Force (PMF) personnel to black spots in Enugu State.